        :markdown
          Late afternoon we arrived at the Greyhound terminal in downtown Las&nbsp;Vegas.

          We split up into two cabs, and made our way from the downtown depot to The Monte Carlo (now called Park MGM Las Vegas), located along the main strip.

  = partial("photoessays/components/photo_full", locals: {slug: current_page.data.slug, caption: '', 'photo': '28/IMG_2494'})

  .Content
    .Row
      .Content_Main.Content_Article
        :markdown
          Traffic in Vegas is rather terrible. As we rode along overpasses and highways, we got our first good look of Vegas proper.
          
          We saw the pyramid shaped Luxor, the castle-themed Excalibur, and New York-New York â€” replete with a statue of liberty, and a rollercoaster built in to its exterior.

          Our taxis soon arrived at the Monte Carlo lobby.

    = partial("photoessays/components/photo_two_column", locals: {slug: current_page.data.slug, 'left': ['28/IMG_2497'], 'right': ['28/IMG_2499'] })

    .Row
      .Content_Main.Content_Article
        :markdown
          The size of the hotel was very impressive, especially having just checked out of Banana Bungalow in Hollywood that morning.    

    = partial("photoessays/components/place_accomodation", locals: {slug: current_page.data.slug, image: '28/IMG_2499', title: 'The Monte Carlo', address: '3770 S Las Vegas Blvd, Las Vegas, NV 89109, USA', checkin: '28 July', checkout: '1 August', rating: 5 })
    
    .Row
      .Content_Main.Content_Article
        :markdown
          We entered the cool, ritzy lobby to check-in. A soon-to-be-familiar artificial, perfumed smell permeated throughout the casino lobby. Over the top, ostentatious archirecture and furnishings adorned the large, luxuriously styled interior.

          I ducked in to line with my Passport and ID, having booked the Las Vegas leg of our accomodation. We had booked two rooms, which ended up being on floors 23 and 28.

    = partial("photoessays/components/photo_grid", locals: {slug: current_page.data.slug, rows: [ { count: 2, caption: 'Genuinely good accomodation HYPE', photos: ['28/IMG_2505','28/IMG_2511'] } ] } )

    .Row
      .Content_Main.Content_Article
        :markdown
          As we waited to check in, an impromptu percussion performance began to promote the Blue Man Group. We, along with many of our fellow lobby occupants, swarmed to watch.

    .Row.pt4.pb4.pl1.pr1
      %video{src: "/#{images_dir}/photoessays/#{current_page.data.slug}/28/IMG_2506_lq.mp4", controls: true, preload: 'metadata'}

    .Row
      .Content_Main.Content_Article
        :markdown
          Once the surprise performance was over, we lugged our bags up to our rooms. Michael, Irwin, and I took one the room on floor 28, and Andrew, Richard, and Jared took the room on floor 23.

    = partial("photoessays/components/photo_right", locals: {slug: current_page.data.slug, caption: '', photo: '28/IMG_2516'})
    
    .Row
      .Content_Main.Content_Article
